cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing and information retrieval, specifically in the context of polysemy and knowledge base construction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which suggests it could also fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with textual data, which could potentially fit into cs.CY (Computers and Society).
